'''ထၜးဆန္ဒဍုင်ဗၟာ ၂၀၂၁''' ('''2021 Myanmar protests''') ဂှ် ဒှ်ညးဍုင်ကွာန် ကောန်ဍုင်ဗၟာ မထ္ၜးဆန္ဒ ဒစဵုဒစး [[ပၞာန်သီအဝဵု ဍုင်ဗၟာ ၂၀၂၁]] နကဵု ဂဥုပ်ဗိုလ်ပၞာန်ဗၟာ မင်းအောင်လှိုင်း ပ္ဍဲကဵု ဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ၁ သၞာံ ၂၀၂၁။<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usnews.com/news/world/articles/2021-02-03/anti-coup-protest-on-streets-of-myanmars-second-city|title=Anti-Coup Protest on Streets of Myanmar's Second City|agency=US News|date=February 3, 2021}}</ref> ၜိုတ် ဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ၁၁၊ ၂၀၂၁ ဂှ် အဆက်အစပ်ဝွံတုဲ မၞိဟ်ၜိုတ် ၂၂၀ တၠ ဒးဒုင်ရပ်။<ref name=":1">{{cite web|date=2021-02-07|title=Daily Briefing in Relation to the Military Coup|url=https://aappb.org/?p=13080|access-date=2021-02-08|website=aappb.org {{!}} Assistance Association for Political Prisoners}}</ref> ထၜးဆန္ဒဂှ် စကၠောန်ဗဒှ် နကဵု နဲကဲၜိုဟ်သြိုဟ် သက္ကုပကီုပရာပ်<ref>{{Cite web|date=2021-02-03|title=Myanmar adopts nonviolent approach to resist army coup|url=https://arab.news/w5msa|access-date=2021-02-07|website=Arab News|language=en}}</ref> မပ္တံကဵု နဲကဲ ညးဍုင်ကွာန် ဟွံကလင်အမိင် (civil disobedience)၊ ဟွံစှ်ေကမၠောန် (labour strikes)၊ ဟွံဆက်ဆောမ် ကုဒပ်ပၞာန် (a military boycott campaign၊ ကာမ်ပိန်ဇုက်ဖေဝ်ဗကေတ် (a red ribbon campaign)၊ တိတ်ထ္ၜးဆန္ဒ၊ ပစၞးသမ္တီ ကုအမာတ်မဇၞးမာဲတအ် ဒှ်တမ်ရ။ 
[[File:Free Daw Aung San Su Kyi.jpg|thumb|ညးထ္ၜးဆန္ဒ ပ္ဍဲဍုင်လ္ဂုင် မရပ်လဝ် "Free Daw Aung San Suu Kyi (ဗလးကဵု ဒဝ်အံင်သာန်သုကျဳ" ပ္ဍဲ ၈ ဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ၂၀၂၁။]]
အသာ်ဗကေတ်ဂှ် ဒှ်အရာမပစၞး ကုဗော်အေန်အေဝ်ဒဳ (NLD) မဒှ်ဗော်ဒဝ်အံင်သာန်သုကျဳတုဲ မၞိဟ်ထၜးဆန္ဒတအ် စကာယာတ်ဗကေတ်ဗွဲဂမၠိုင်ရ။<ref>{{cite web|last=CNN|first=Carly Walsh and Akanksha Sharma|title=Protests break out in Myanmar in defiance of military coup|url=https://www.cnn.com/2021/02/06/asia/protests-myanmar-military-coup-intl-hnk/index.html|access-date=2021-02-07|website=cnn.com}}</ref> တုဲပၠန် ဒွက်ဗၟာ (ကမ္ဘာမကျေဘူး) မဒှ်ဒွက် မစကာလဝ် ပ္ဍဲအခိင်ထၜးဆန္ဒ ၁၉၈၈ တေအ်ဂှ် နဒဒှ် ဒွက်ချဳဓရာင် ပရေင်ဍုင်ကွာန် ပ္ဍဲကဵုထၜးဆန္ဒဏီဂှ် စကာလဝ် ဗွဲမဂၠိုင်ရ။<ref>{{Cite web|date=2021-02-06|title=Myanmar restaurant in Bangkok promotes anti-coup activity|url=https://apnews.com/article/aung-san-suu-kyi-myanmar-coronavirus-pandemic-bangkok-thailand-a3759daec75ab8d6104c7e86becc07c2|access-date=2021-02-08|website=AP NEWS}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=2021-02-04|title=Resistance to coup grows despite Myanmar's block of Facebook|url=https://apnews.com/article/myanmar-blocks-facebook-08ce7dd971655e839d6a81e7391d9e4f|access-date=2021-02-08|website=AP NEWS}}</ref><ref name=":23">{{cite web|date=2018-08-09|title=Songwriter Who Provided "Theme Song" to 8888 Uprising Finally Honored|url=https://www.irrawaddy.com/news/burma/songwriter-provided-theme-song-8888-uprising-finally-honored.html|access-date=2021-02-04|magazine=The Irrawaddy}}</ref> ပတိုန်လပုဟ်တဲလဒေါဝ်ပိဂှ်လေဝ် နဒဒှ်သင်္ကေတ ထၜးဆန္ဒဂှ် စကာကၠုင်ရ။<ref>{{cite web|author1=|first=|author2=|date=Feb 5, 2021|title=Myanmar blocks Facebook as resistance grows to military coup|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2021-02-05/myanmar-blocks-facebook-as-resistance-grows-to-military-coup/13124148|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=5 February 2021|website=|publisher=ABC News (Australia)}}</ref> 
ထၜးဆန္ဒဂှ် ဗွဲကိုပ်ကၠာ စကတဵုဒှ် သွက်ဂွံဗလးကဵု ဒဝ်အံင်သာန်သုကျဳ ကေုာံ သမ္မတ ဦးဝေန်မျေအ် ကေုာံ ညံင်ဂွံပဒတန် သွဟ်မာဲ အတိုင်ကမ္မရှေန်မာဲ မလလောင်တြးလဝ်ကီုလေဝ် ဗွဲကြဴ နကဵုကွးဘာတက္ကသိုလ်တအ်ဂှ် ဗၟံက်ကၠုင်ရုပ်ရဴ ဗတိုက်သရိုဟ် တၠအဝဵုပၞာန်တုဲ ညံင်ဍုင် ဂွံဒှ် ဍုင်ဒဳမဝ်ကရေသဳဇေတ်တ်ရ။ နကဵုကောန်ဍုင်အရင် မပ္တံကဵု မန်၊ ကရေင်၊ ပအိုအ်တအ်ဂှ် ချဳဓရာင်ကၠုင် သွက်ဂွံဗတိုက်သရိုဟ် တၠအဝဵုသီုဖအိုတ်၊ ပလီုသဇိုင်သၞောဝ် ၂၀၀၈၊ ညံင်ဂွံဒက်ပ္တန် သၞောတ်ဖေဝ်ဒရေဝ်ဒဳမဝ်ကရေသဳ မြဴသာ်ဝွံ အရာတၞဟ်ခြာ အကြာ ဂကောံမအာဂတပၠတရဴ ထၜးဆန္ဒတအ် နွံကၠုင်ရ။ 

== ဒဒှ်အတိက် ==
{{main|ပၞာန်သီအဝဵု ဍုင်ဗၟာ ၂၀၂၁}}

ပၞာန်ထိင်ထောအ်အဝဵုဍုင် စကတဵုဒှ် ပ္ဍဲအခိင်ဂယး ပ္ဍဲစၟတ်တ္ၚဲ ၁ ဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ၂၀၂၁၊ နကဵု ဒပ်ပၞာန်တအ် သီကေတ်အဝဵု နူကဵု ဗော်အေန်အေဝ်ဒဳ ညးမကလိဂွံဇမၞးမာဲ ပ္ဍဲသဘင်မာဲ ၂၀၂၀ တုဲ ဒက်ပ္တန် ကံင်သဳစၟိန်ပြမာန်ဍုင်။ နကဵု ပၞာန် လလောင်တြး အကာဲအရာကာတၟေင် ပွိုင်မွဲသၞာံတုဲ အဝဵုဍုင်သီုဖအိုတ်ဂှ် ပအပ်ကဵု သကိုပ် ကဍိုက်ကဍိုပ်ပရေင်စဵုဒၞာ(ဒပ်ပၞာန်) မင်းအောင်လှိုင်း။ လလောင်တြး အကာဲအရာကာတၟေင်ဂှ် ကတဵုဒှ် ပ္ဍဲတ္ၚဲ ကိုပ်ကၠာ မဟွံဂွံစပံက်စၠတ်ထဝ်ကၟိန်ဍုင်ရ။<ref>{{cite web|last=|first=|date=1 February 2021|title=Myanmar military seizes power, detains elected leader Aung San Suu Kyi|url=https://news.trust.org/item/20210201014444-5u7cm|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210201053645/https://news.trust.org/item/20210201014444-5u7cm|archive-date=1 February 2021|access-date=1 February 2021|website=Thomson Reuters Foundation News|agency=Reuters}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=|first=|date=1 February 2021|editor=|title=Myanmar gov't declares 1-year state of emergency: President's Office|url=http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2021-02/01/c_139712581.htm|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210201102057/http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2021-02/01/c_139712581.htm|archive-date=1 February 2021|access-date=1 February 2021|website=|agency=Xinhua News Agency}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Myanmar Leader Aung San Suu Kyi, Others Detained by Military|url=https://www.voanews.com/east-asia-pacific/myanmar-leader-aung-san-suu-kyi-others-detained-military|date=1 February 2021|website=voanews.com|publisher=VOA (Voice of America)|access-date=1 February 2021|archive-date=3 February 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210203131316/https://www.voanews.com/east-asia-pacific/myanmar-leader-aung-san-suu-kyi-others-detained-military|url-status=live}}</ref>သမ္မတဍုင်ဗၟာ ဦးဝင်မြင့် ကေုာံ ညးမကဵုကသပ်ဍုင် ဒဝ်အံင်သာန်သုကျဳ ဒးဒုင်ကြိုင်၊ ကရောမ်ဂှ် ဝန်ဇၞော် ကေုာံ မၞိဟ်အဓိကတၞဟ်တအ်လေဝ် ဒးဒုင် ရပ်တၟာဂလိုင်ကီုရ။<ref name=":0">{{cite news|last=Beech|first=Hannah|date=31 January 2021|title=Myanmar's Leader, Daw Aung San Suu Kyi, Is Detained Amid Coup|newspaper=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/31/world/asia/myanmar-coup-suu-kyi.html|access-date=31 January 2021|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=31 January 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210131235036/https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/31/world/asia/myanmar-coup-suu-kyi.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Mahtani|first1=Shibani|author2=Kyaw Ye Lynn |title=Myanmar military seizes power in coup after detaining Aung San Suu Kyi|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/asia_pacific/myanmar-aung-sun-suu-kyi-arrest/2021/01/31/c780ce6a-6419-11eb-886d-5264d4ceb46d_story.html|date=1 February 2021|access-date=1 February 2021|newspaper=The Washington Post|archive-date=1 February 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210201182106/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/asia_pacific/myanmar-aung-sun-suu-kyi-arrest/2021/01/31/c780ce6a-6419-11eb-886d-5264d4ceb46d_story.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

== လဒက်ပ္တန် ညးဍုင်ကွာန် ဒစဵုဒစး ==
=== Civil disobedience movement and labour strikes ===
[[File:Protest against military coup (9 Feb 2021, Hpa-An, Kayin State, Myanmar) (3).jpg|thumb|မၞိဟ်မဗိုက်လတက်လဝ် ကယိုင်အစာဘာ ထ္ၜးဆန္ဒ ပ္ဍဲဍုင်ဖာအင် ပ္ဍဲ ၉ ဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ၂၀၂၁။]]

ပ္ဍဲ ၂ ဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ၂၀၂၁၊ သၟာကမၠောန်ထတ်ယုက် ကေုာံ ညးဂလိုင်သၟိင်တၠ အလုံမွဲဍုင် သီုကဵု ပ္ဍဲနေပျဳတဝ် ချဳဓရာင်မဟွံကလင်အမိင် (a national civil disobedience movement) (အာဏာဖီဆန်ရေးလှုပ်ရှားမှု)၊ ဟိုတ်နူကဵု ပၞာန်သီအဝဵုဍုင်။<ref>{{cite web|date=2 February 2021|title=Nay Pyi Taw, Mandalay healthcare staff to join "Civil Disobedience Campaign"|url=https://www.mmtimes.com/news/nay-pyi-taw-mandalay-healthcare-staff-join-civil-disobedience-campaign.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210203131330/https://www.mmtimes.com/news/nay-pyi-taw-mandalay-healthcare-staff-join-civil-disobedience-campaign.html|archive-date=3 February 2021|access-date=2 February 2021|newspaper=The Myanmar Times}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|date=2 February 2021|title=Myanmar Medics Prepare Civil Disobedience Against Military Rule|url=https://www.irrawaddy.com/news/burma/myanmar-medics-prepare-civil-disobedience-military-rule.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210203131324/https://www.irrawaddy.com/news/burma/myanmar-medics-prepare-civil-disobedience-military-rule.html|archive-date=3 February 2021|access-date=2 February 2021 |magazine=The Irrawaddy}}</ref> ကာမ်ပိန် ဝှုက်ၜောက် နကဵုယၟု "Civil Disobedience Movement" ဂှ် မၞိဟ်ပါလုပ် 230,000 ပြင်င် အပ္ဍဲပွိုင် ပိ-ပန်တ္ၚဲဂှ်။<ref name=":11">{{cite web |date=2021-02-03|title=Teachers, students join anti-coup campaign as hospital staff stop work|url=https://www.frontiermyanmar.net/en/teachers-students-join-anti-coup-campaign-as-hospital-staff-stop-work/ |access-date=2021-02-03|website=Frontier Myanmar}}</ref><ref name=":8">{{cite web|last=|first=|date=2021-02-02|title=After coup, medical workers spearhead civil disobedience campaign|url=https://www.frontiermyanmar.net/en/after-coup-medical-workers-spearhead-civil-disobedience-campaign/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210203131438/https://www.frontiermyanmar.net/en/after-coup-medical-workers-spearhead-civil-disobedience-campaign/|archive-date=3 February 2021|access-date=2021-02-02|website=Frontier Myanmar}}</ref><ref name=":29">{{Cite web|date=2021-02-09|title=EXPLAINER: How are the Myanmar protests being organized?|url=https://apnews.com/article/technology-aung-san-suu-kyi-myanmar-yangon-asia-pacific-026ad5eb9ad6920f0d0d5446e17e27c2|access-date=2021-02-10|website=AP NEWS}}</ref>မေန်ကဝ်နာင် (မင်းကိုနိုင်) က္ဍိုပ်သကိုပ်ကွးဘာ ၈၈၈၈ ဆဝ်ဗ္ၚုဟ် ညးဍုင်ကွာန် "ဟွံစၟတ်သမ္တီ၊ ဟွံပါလုပ် (no recognition, no participation)" သွက်ဂွံ ဒစဵုဒစး အလဵုအသဳပၞာန်ရ။<ref>{{cite web|title=Veteran activist calls for civil disobedience in wake of coup|url=https://www.myanmar-now.org/en/news/veteran-activist-calls-for-civil-disobedience-in-wake-of-coup|access-date=2021-02-04|agency=Myanmar NOW}}</ref> 

သၟာကမၠောန်ထတ်ယုက် နူကဵု ရုင်ဂဥုဲအလဵုအသဳ ၜိုတ်မွဲဒါဇြေန် မလလောင်တြးဟွံစှ်ေကမၠောန်ဂှ် စကတဵုဒှ် နူကဵု ဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ၃၊ ၂၀၂၁။<ref name=":8"/><ref>{{cite web|author1=Matthew Tostevin|author2=Grant McCool|author3=Stephen Coates|date=3 February 2021|title=Myanmar doctors stop work to protest coup as UN considers response|url=https://www.afr.com/world/asia/myanmar-doctors-stop-work-to-protest-coup-as-un-considers-response-20210203-p56z7z|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210203131358/https://www.afr.com/world/asia/myanmar-doctors-stop-work-to-protest-coup-as-un-considers-response-20210203-p56z7z|archive-date=3 February 2021|access-date=3 February 2021|publisher=Financial Review}}</ref> စနူ ၃ ဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ၂၀၂၁ သၟာကမၠောန်ထတ်ယုက် နူကဵု ရုင်ဂဥုဲ ကေုာံ ဌာနထတ်ယုက် ၜိုတ် ၁၁၀<ref name=":12">{{cite web|date=2021-02-03|title=Myanmar's Medics Launch Civil Disobedience Campaign Against Coup|url=https://www.irrawaddy.com/news/burma/myanmars-medics-launch-civil-disobedience-campaign-coup.html |access-date=2021-02-04|magazine=The Irrawaddy}}</ref> ပါလုပ် ပ္ဍဲပရေင်ချဳဓရာင်ဂှ်။<ref name=":11"/> ပ္ဍဲမၞိဟ် ၁၃ ဂှ် မၞိဟ်တြဴတၠဂှ် နူကဵု ကမ္မတဳဇၞော်မောဝ်ဍုင် မာန္တလေ (မန္တလေ စည်းပင်) သီုကဵု ဒုမြုဝန် ရဲမွန် (vice-mayor Ye Mon) ပတိုန်လိက် နုက်တိတ် နူကမၠောန်၊ နကဵုမထ္ၜး ဒစဵုဒစး ပၞာန်သီအဝဵုဍုင်။<ref>{{cite web|date=2021-02-03|title=Mandalay vice mayor, MCDC members resign|url=https://www.mmtimes.com/news/mandalay-vice-mayor-mcdc-members-resign.html|access-date=2021-02-03|newspaper=The Myanmar Times}}</ref> သၟာကမၠောန်ဟွံစှ်ေကမၠောန်တအ်ဂှ် ဒးဒုင် ဓရတ် ဘပဠ ကတဵုဒှ်ကၠုင်ရ။<ref>{{Cite web|date=2021-02-05|title=Government medics receive threats for civil disobedience campaign|url=https://www.frontiermyanmar.net/en/government-medics-receive-threats-for-civil-disobedience-campaign/|access-date=2021-02-07|website=Frontier Myanmar|language=en-US}}</ref> စနူ ဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ၉ ဂှ် ကမၠောန်ထပက် ဝက်သိန် ယဲကဝ်ဝိဒ်-၁၉ ဂှ် ဒးဒေါအ်ဇူထောအ်၊ ရုင်ဂဥုဲ ပ္ဍဲဍုင်ဗၟာ ဗွဲဂမၠိုင် ဒးကၟာတ်လဝ်ရ။<ref>{{cite news |title=Health Care Feels The Pinch as Myanmar Medical Workers Join Civil Disobedience Movement |url=https://www.rfa.org/english/news/myanmar/health-care-02092021173347.html |access-date=10 February 2021 |work=Radio Free Asia |date=9 February 2021 |language=en}}</ref>

သၟာကမၠောန်ဟွံစှ်ေကမၠောန် ဗွဲမပြဟ် ကၠောအ်ကၞာန်အာ ဌာနတၞဟ်တအ်ရ။ ဂကောံအစာဘာထပှ်ဂကောံ သီုကဵု ဂကောံအစာဘာဍုင်ဗၟာ မနွံကဵု ဒြဟတ်မွဲကိုဋ်ဂှ် ပံင်တောဲ မဟွံစှ်ေကမၠောန်ဂှ်ကီုရ။<ref name=":11"/> ကောန်ကမၠောန် နူကဵု ဌာနဝန်ဇၞော်ကာဍုင်သအာင် မဒှ်ဌာန သၟဝ်ဒဝ်အံင်သာန်သုကျဳဂှ်လေဝ် ပံင်တောဲ မဟွံစှ်ေကမၠောန်ကီုရ။<ref name=":12"/> ပ္ဍဲ ၄ ဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ၂၀၂၁ ပ္ဍဲနေပျဳတဝ် သၟာကမၠောန် နူဌာနဝန်ဇၞော်တဵုလွဳ ကေုာံ ဇွောအ်မ (Ministry of Agriculture, Livestock and Irrigation) တိတ်ထ္ၜးဆန္ဒ။<ref>{{cite web|title=စစ်အစိုးရကို နေပြည်တော်က နိုင်ငံ့ဝန်ထမ်းတွေ ကန့်ကွက်ဆန္ဒပြ|url=https://www.rfa.org/burmese/news/nld-government-staff-against-military-coup-02042021030530.html|access-date=2021-02-04|publisher=Radio Free Asia|language=my}}</ref> ပ္ဍဲ ၅ ဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ၂၀၂၁ သၟာကမၠောန်မာင်ဗရိုတ် နူကဵုဒဵုကျဳသိန်တံင် (Kyisintaung copper mines) ပံင်တောဲ ကာမ်ပိန် မဟွံစှ်ေကမၠောန်။<ref name="Irrawaddy_6Feb_copper_miners"/> သၟာကမၠောန်တအ် ညးတအ် ဆက်ဒစဵုဒစး မဟွံစှ်ေကမၠောန် စဵုကဵု "က္ဍိုပ်သကိုပ် မရုဲစှ် ကလေင်ကလိဂွံ အဝဵုဍုင်ပၠန်"။<ref name="Irrawaddy_6Feb_copper_miners"/>
[[File:Teenagers are protesting while wearing skirt in Mawlamyine (9 February 2021).jpg|thumb|မၞိဟ်မကျိုင်လဝ် ကယျိုင်အစာဘာ ထ္ၜးဆန္ဒ ပ္ဍဲဍုင်မတ်မလီု ပ္ဍဲ ၁၁ ဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ၂၀၂၁။]]
ပ္ဍဲ ၅ ဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ၂၀၂၁ ပရေင်ချဳဒရာင် ညးဍုင်ကွာန်ဒစဵုဒစး ဂှ် ကတဵုဒှ်ကၠုင် ပ္ဍဲကဵုဌာနပရေင်အုပ်ဓုပ်၊ ဂဥုဲ၊ ပညာ "ရုင်ဂဥုဲအလဵုအသဳ ၉၁၊ တက္ကသိုလ် ကေုာံ ကဝ်လိက် ၁၈၊ ကေုာံ ဌာနရုင်အလဵုအသဳ ၁၂ ဌာန နူကဵု ၇၉ ပွိုင်ဍုင်"။<ref name="Irrawaddy_5Feb_strike"/> နန်းနွေ၊ နူကဵု ဌာနစိတ္တဗေဒ တက္ကသိုလ်လ္ဂုင် ဟီု၊ "ပိုယ်မဒှ်မၞိဟ် မဗတောန်ကွးဘာတအ် သွက်ဂွံသၟာန် ကၠိုဟ် ပရူဓဝ်ဍာံဂှ် နကဵုနဲလဵုလေဝ် ပိုယ်ဂွံဒုင်တဲ အရာမသက္ကုဓဝ်ဍာံ ဟွံမာန်"။<ref name="Irrawaddy_6Feb_protests"/><ref>{{cite web|date=2021-02-05|title=Civilian Disobedience Campaign' takes flight in Myanmar|url=https://www.mmtimes.com/news/civilian-disobedience-campaign-takes-flight-myanmar.html|access-date=2021-02-05|newspaper=The Myanmar Times}}</ref>

ပ္ဍဲ ၈ ဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ဂှ် လိက်ပရိုင်ဍုင် ကြေးမှုန်း ကဵု မြန်မာ့အလင်း ချူညံင်ညးဍုင်ကွာန် ဂွံဒေါအ်ထောအ် နူကဵုပွမဒစဵုဒစး အလဵုအသဳပၞာန်။<ref name=":20">{{Cite web|date=2021-02-08|title=Media group worries over press freedom in Myanmar under military rule|url=https://www.mmtimes.com/news/media-group-worries-over-press-freedom-myanmar-under-military-rule.html|access-date=2021-02-08|website=The Myanmar Times}}</ref> ဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ၈ ဂှ် ဘာဏ်ကမ္ဘောဇ ဒးကၟာတ်ထောအ် ရုင်မွဲလစုတ် ဟိုတ်နူကဵု ကောန်ကမၠောန် ပါလုပ်ပ္ဍဲကဵု ကာမ်ပိန်မဟွံကလင်အမိင်။<ref name=":21">{{Cite web|date=2021-02-08|title=KBZ Bank temporarily shuts down all branches|url=https://www.mmtimes.com/news/kbz-bank-temporarily-shuts-down-all-branches.html|access-date=2021-02-08|website=The Myanmar Times}}</ref> ဗီုဂှ် ပ္ဍဲကဵု ဘာဏ်တၞဟ်တအ်လေဝ် ဒးဆဵုဂဗ ညိညကီုရ။<ref name=":21" /> ဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ၉ ဂှ် ကောန်ကမၠောန် နူကဵု ဘာဏ်ဗဟဵုဍုင်ဗၟာ ပံင်တောဲ ပါလုပ် ပ္ဍဲကဵု ပရေင်ချဳဓရာင်ဂှ်။<ref>{{Cite web|date=2021-02-10|title=Central Bank of Myanmar Staff Join Anti-Coup Protests|url=https://www.irrawaddy.com/news/burma/central-bank-myanmar-staff-join-anti-coup-protests.html|access-date=2021-02-10|website=The Irrawaddy|language=en-US}}</ref>

၉ ဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ဂှ် နူကဵု ဌာနဝန်ဇၞော်ထတ်ယုက် ချူတြး ပ္ဍဲပရိုင် မြန်မာ့အလင်း ညံင်ကောန်ကမၠောန်ထတ်ယုက်တအ် ဂွံကလေင်စှ်ေကမၠောန်။<ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=2021-02-09|title=Request To Health Workers|url=https://www.gnlm.com.mm/request-to-health-workers/|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2021-02-10|website=Global New Light Of Myanmar|language=en-US}}</ref> ဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ၁၀ ဂှ် နူကဵု သမဂ္ဂသၟာကမၠောန်တအ် ဒစဵုဒစး လတူတၠကမၠောန် မဓရတ် ကောန်ကမၠောန် ကုညးမပါလုပ် ပ္ဍဲကာမ်ပိန်တအ်ရ။<ref>{{Cite web|date=2021-02-10|title=Trade union in Myanmar to prosecute those taking legal action against CDM participants|url=https://www.mmtimes.com/news/trade-union-myanmar-prosecute-those-taking-legal-action-against-cdm-participants.html|access-date=2021-02-10|website=The Myanmar Times}}</ref>

=== ကာမ်ပိန် ဗဂပ်ဗဗေင် အရာမဆက်စပ် ကုဒပ်ပၞာန် <br>Military boycott campaign ===
[[File:MYANMAR BEER AT THE NEW DOREEN RESTAURANT YANGON MYANMAR JAN 2013 (8492498537).jpg|thumb|Myanmar Beer ဒးဒုင်ဗဂပ်ဗဗေင် ဟိုတ်နူကဵု ကမ္မဏဳ မပ္တိတ်ဗဳယာဏအ် ဆက်စပ်ဒၟံင် ကုဒပ်ပၞာန်။]]
ပ္ဍဲ ၃ ဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ၂၀၂၁ ပရေင်ချဳဓရာင် ညးဍုင်ကွာန်မွဲ ဆဝ်ဗ္ၚုဟ် "ဒေါအ်ထောအ် နူမရာန်ကပေါတ်တၠအဝဵု (Stop Buying Junta Business)" မဒှ်ကာမ်ပိန် ကပေါတ်မဆက်စပ် ကုပရေင်ပိုန်ဒြပ် ဒပ်ပၞာန်သီုဖအိုတ် လ္ပရာန် လ္ပကဵုဒြဟတ်ရ။<ref name=":13">{{cite web|date=2021-02-03|title=Myanmar calls for boycott of Tatmadaw linked products and services|url=https://www.mmtimes.com/news/myanmar-calls-boycott-tatmadaw-linked-products-and-services.html|access-date=2021-02-03|newspaper=The Myanmar Times}}</ref> ကပေါတ် မပိုင်ပြဳ နကဵုဒပ်ပၞာန် ကေုာံ မဆက်စပ် ကုဒပ်ပၞာန်ဂှ် ကမ္မဏဳဖုန် Mytel၊ ကမ္မဏဳဗဳယ Myanmar Beer၊ Mandalay Beer ကေုာံ Dagon Beer တုဲပၠန် ဆေင်ဍာ်လက်ဖက် ကေုာံ ကဝ်ဖဳ ဗွဲမဂၠိုင်၊ 7th Sense Creation မဒှ်ဆေင် မပံင်တောဲ ကုကောန်ဝုတ် ဂဥုပ်ဗိုလ်ပၞာန် မင်းအောင်လှိုင်၊<ref name=":22">{{cite web|title=Military Chief's Family Members Spend Big on Blockbuster Movies, Beauty Pageants|url=https://www.myanmar-now.org/en/news/military-chiefs-family-members-spend-big-on-blockbuster-movies-beauty-pageants|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201215082136/https://www.myanmar-now.org/en/news/military-chiefs-family-members-spend-big-on-blockbuster-movies-beauty-pageants|archive-date=15 December 2020|access-date=11 January 2021|agency=Myanmar NOW}}</ref> ကေုာံ ကွဳစက်ဂဒေါအ် (bus lines)ဂမၠိုင်လေဝ် နွံကီုရ။<ref name=":13" /> 

စပ်ကဵု ကာမ်ပိန်ဏအ်တုဲ အေန်ဂျေန်နဳယာ ၇၁ တၠ မကၠောန်ဒၟံင် သွက် Mytel ပ္ဍဲရးသဂိုင်ဂှ် တိတ်ထောအ် နူကမၠောန် နဒဒှ် ဒစဵုဒစး။<ref name=":11" /> ဖျာလ္ၚဵု ကၠဟ်ပ္တိတ်ထောအ် Myanmar Beer နူကဵု ဖျာ။<ref>{{Cite web|date=2021-02-08|title=MYANMAR PROTESTS LIVE: Tens of thousands gathering in Yangon, demonstrations in other major cities|url=https://www.frontiermyanmar.net/en/myanmar-protests-live-tens-of-thousands-gathering-in-yangon-demonstrations-in-other-major-cities/|access-date=2021-02-08|website=Frontier Myanmar|language=en-US}}</ref>

ပ္ဍဲ ၅ ဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ဂှ် ကမ္မတဳကိရိန် (Kirin Company) ဒေါအ်ထောအ် နူကဵု ပွမပံင်တောဲ ကု Myanma Economic Holdings Limited (MEHL)မဒှ် ကမ္မဏဳပၞာန်မပိုင်ပြဳ။<ref name=":192">{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=|title=Japan's Kirin ends Myanmar beer tie-up with army-owned partner after coup|url=https://news.trust.org/item/20210205070108-ktqjw/|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2021-02-08|website=Thomson Reuters Foundation}}</ref> ပရေင်ပံင်ကောံ joint venture, Myanmar Brewery, ဂှ် ပ္တိတ်ဒၟံင် ဗဳယာမဂၠိုင်ကဵု သွာင် သီုကဵု Myanmar Beer တုဲ နကဵုပရေင်ပံင်ကောံဏအ်ဂှ် ကလိဂွံလဝ် ဗွဝ်ဖျာ ပ္ဍဲဍုင်ဗၟာ ၈၀%။<ref name=":192" /> Kirin's stake ဂှ် နွံကဵု တမ်ရိုဟ်င္ၚုဟ်မ US$1.7 ဗဳလဳယာန်။<ref name=":192" /> ပ္ဍဲ ၈ ဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ Lim Kaling, ညးမပါလုပ် ပ္ဍဲအရာမဒက်ပ္တန် Razer Inc. လလောင်တြး ညးပ္တိတ်ထောအ် ပရေင်ဓလိုက်တမ်ရိုဟ် ပ္ဍဲကဵု ပရေင်ပံင်ကောံ joint venture မဒှ် ကမ္မဏဳၜံက်ဂကူသင်္ဂပူရ် မပိုင်ပြဳလဝ် သတံက် ၄၉% ပ္ဍဲကဵု Virginia Tobacco မဒှ် ဒၞာဲရုင်မပ္တိတ်ၜံက် နကဵုပိုင်ပြဳလဝ် နူကဵု MEHL။<ref name=":26">{{Cite web|last=hermesauto|date=2021-02-09|title=Razer co-founder and director Lim Kaling pulls out of Myanmar joint venture|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/business/companies-markets/razer-co-founder-and-director-lim-kaling-pulls-out-of-myanmar-joint|access-date=2021-02-09|website=The Straits Times|language=en}}</ref> 

=== ပရေင်ချဳဓရာင် တက်စေဝ်<br>Pot-banging movement ===
စတမ်နူ ပၞာန်သီအဝဵုဂှ်ရ မၞိဟ်ပ္ဍဲဒေသ မပ္တံကဵု ဍုင်လ္ဂုင် ကၠောန်ဗဒှ်ပရေင်ချဳဓရာင် တက်စေဝ် ဇၟာပ်ပ်သဝ်တ္ၚဲ ဒစာံနာဍဳ မထ္ၜးသင်္ကေတ ထဍေင်ပ္တိတ်ဟွံခိုဟ် ဟွံသြန်။<ref>{{cite web|date=2021-02-04|title=Myanmar coup: army blocks Facebook access as civil disobedience grows|url=http://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2021/feb/04/myanmar-coup-army-blocks-facebook-access-as-civil-disobedience-grows|access-date=2021-02-04|newspaper=The Guardian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|date=2 February 2021|title=Anti-coup protests ring out in Myanmar's main city|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-politics/anti-coup-protests-ring-out-in-myanmars-main-city-idUSKBN2A139S|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210203131442/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-politics/anti-coup-protests-ring-out-in-myanmars-main-city-idUSKBN2A139S|archive-date=3 February 2021|access-date=3 February 2021|agency=Reuters}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Myanmar coup latest: UN Security Council stops short of issuing statement|url=https://asia.nikkei.com/Spotlight/Myanmar-Coup/Myanmar-coup-latest-UN-Security-Council-stops-short-of-issuing-statement|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210203015938/https://asia.nikkei.com/Spotlight/Myanmar-Coup/Myanmar-coup-latest-UN-Security-Council-stops-short-of-issuing-statement|archive-date=3 February 2021|access-date=2021-02-02|publisher=Nikkei Asia}}</ref> ပ္ဍဲဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ၅ ဂှ် မၞိဟ် ၃၀ တၠဒးဒုင်စောဲဒုဟ် ကုဗၠာဲသၟိင် နကဵုပိုဒ်ဇၞော် ၄၇ ဟိုတ်နူမညာန်တက်စေဝ်။<ref>{{cite web|title=30 arrested in Mandalay for pot-banging movement in protest against military coup|url=https://elevenmyanmar.com/news/30-arrested-in-mandalay-for-pot-banging-movement-in-protest-against-military-coup|access-date=2021-02-06|newspaper=Eleven Media Group Co., Ltd}}</ref>

=== ထၜးဆန္ဒ တိတ်မ္ၚး<br>Public protests ===
[[File:Protest against military coup (9 Feb 2021, Hpa-An, Kayin State, Myanmar) (1).jpg|thumb|People from [[Hpa-an]] protesting against military coup (9 February 2021)]]
ပ္ဍဲ ၂ ဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ၂၀၂၁ ဂှ် ပ္ဍဲလ္ဂုင် မၞိဟ်ညိည တိတ်ထ္ၜးဆန္ဒ ၜိုတ် ၁၅ မိနေတ် ပ္ဍဲအခိင်ဒေသ ၂၀း၀၀ အာတ်မိက် ညံင်ဂွံကလေင်ပအပ်ကဵုအဝဵု ကေုာံ ဗလးကဵု ဒဝ်အံင်သာန်သုကျဳ။<ref>{{cite web|title=စစ်အာဏာသိမ်းမှုကို အနုနည်းအာဏာဖီဆန်မှု တချို့ရှိလာခြင်း|url=https://burmese.voanews.com/a/myanmar-civil-disobedience-movement-/5762587.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210203131338/https://burmese.voanews.com/a/myanmar-civil-disobedience-movement-/5762587.html|archive-date=3 February 2021|access-date=2021-02-02|website=ဗွီအိုအေ|language=my}}</ref> ဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ၄ ဂှ် မၞိဟ် ၃၀ တၠ ထ္ၜးဆန္ဒ ဂတမုက်ဘာတက္ကသိုလ်ဂဥုဲမာန္တလေ ပ္ဍဲဍုင်မာန္တလေ၊ ပ္ဍဲဂှ် မၞိဟ် ၄ တၠ ဒးဒုင်ရပ်။<ref>{{cite web |date=2021-02-04|title=Mandalay citizens protest against Tatmadaw rule|url=https://www.mmtimes.com/news/mandalay-citizens-protest-against-tatmadaw-rule.html|access-date=2021-02-04|newspaper=The Myanmar Times}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Four arrested in Mandalay after street protest against military coup|url=https://www.myanmar-now.org/en/news/four-arrested-in-mandalay-after-street-protest-against-military-coup |access-date=2021-02-04|agency=Myanmar NOW}}</ref>
[[File:2021 Civil Disobedience at Hledan.jpg|thumb|A protester waves the red NLD flag at Yangon's Hledan Junction.]]
ပ္ဍဲ ၆ ဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ၂၀၂၁ ထၜးဆန္ဒ နကဵုမၞိဟ်ဗွဲမဂၠိုင်ဂှ် စကတဵုဒှ်ကၠုင် အပ္ဍဲဍုင်ဗၟာ။<ref>{{cite web|last=CNN|first=Carly Walsh and Akanksha Sharma|title=Protests break out in Myanmar in defiance of military coup |url=https://www.cnn.com/2021/02/06/asia/protests-myanmar-military-coup-intl-hnk/index.html|access-date=2021-02-07|publisher=CNN}}</ref> ထၜးဆန္ဒဂှ် ကတဵုဒှ်ကၠုင် ဗွဲမဂၠိုင် မသက္ကုက္ဍိုက်သကိုပ်တုဲ ဗီုညးကဵုညး တိတ်ကၠုင်ဂၠံင်။<ref name=":29" /> ပ္ဍဲတ္ၚဲဂှ် ပ္ဍဲဍုင်လ္ဂုင် မၞိဟ်ၜိုတ် 20,000 တိတ်ထ္ၜးဆန္ဒ မဒစဵုဒစး ပၞာန်သီအဝဵု၊ အာတ်မိက် ညံင်ဂွံဗလးကဵု ဒဝ်အံင်သာန်သုကျဳ ကရေဲ "တၠအဝဵုပၞာန် ကဵုကျညိ၊ ကဵုကျညိ၊ ဒဳမဝ်ကရေသဳ သ္ဒးဇၞးရောင် သ္ဒးဇၞးရောင် နကဵု ဘာသာဗၟာ။ လစဝ် (ညးဒဳကွဳစက်)တအ် ပတ်ဟန် နဒဒှ် မထံက်ဂလာန်။ ကာလညးတအ် စိုပ် ဂၠံင်ပန်သွာင် (ဂၠံင်အင်စိင်-လှည်းတန်) ဂှ် ဗၠာဲသၟိင်တအ် ကၟာတ်ဟွံကဵု ဆက်အာဂတ။<ref name="AJE_6Feb_protestors_standoff"/> ပ္ဍဲဂှ် သၟာကမၠောန် နူကဵု ဂကောံသၟာကမၠောန် ၁၄ ဂကောံပံင်တောဲပါလုပ်။ ဗီုရုပ်တအ်ဂှ် ဗလးထ္ၜးဒၟံင် ပ္ဍဲဝှုက်ၜေါက်တုဲ မၞိဟ်စိုတ်လုပ်စဂၠိုင်၊ ဆဂး အခိင်ၜိုတ် ၁၄း၀၀ ဂှ် မၞိဟ်အောန်စှ်ေအာ။ ကွဳစက်ပါက်ဍာ် ဗၠာဲသၟိင်ဂှ် စဵုဒၞာစွံလဝ် ပ္ဍဲသူလေ။<ref name="Irrawaddy_6Feb_protests"/> သဝ်တ္ၚဲညိဂှ် ပ္ဍဲမာန္တလေ၊ ပျေန်မနာတအ်လေဝ် စထ္ၜးကၠုင်ဆန္ဒဇၞော်ဇၞော်ကီု။ ပ္ဍဲမာန္တလေဂှ် စတိတ် ပ္ဍဲအခိင် ၁၃း၀၀၊ ထၜးဆန္ဒ ဆက်ကၠောန်အာ နကဵု ကွဳလိုင်ဓါတ် စဵုကဵု ၁၆း၀၀။ ၜိုတ် ၁၈း၀၀ ဂှ် ဗၠာဲသၟိင်တအ် ထိင် ထၜးဆန္ဒမာန်အာ။<ref name="Irrawaddy_6Feb_protests" />

[[File:2021 Kyaukse anti-military protesting.webm |thumb|upright=| Many people protesting against the military coup on the main road in [[Kyaukse]].]]
ပ္ဍဲ ၇ ဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ဂှ် ထၜးဆန္ဒဂှ် ပြးကၞာန်အာ အပ္ဍဲဍုင် ပ္ဍဲကဵုဍုင်ရးဗွဲမဂၠိုင်။ မၞိဟ်ဂၠိုင်အိုတ်ဂှ် ပ္ဍဲလ္ဂုင် မၞိဟ်ဒှ်အာၜိုတ် 150,000 ဇက်တိုန် အဝိုင်လှည်းတန် ကေုာံ ကျာ်စုလောဟ် ပ္ဍဲလဒေါဝ်ဍုင်လ္ဂုင်။<ref name=":10">{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=2021-02-07|title=စစ်အာဏာသိမ်းဆန့်ကျင်မှု ရန်ကုန်မြို့ခံသိန်းနဲ့ချီ စုဝေး|url=https://burmese.voanews.com/a/military-coup-myanmar-protest/5768496.html|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2021-02-07|website=ဗွီအိုအေ|language=my}}</ref><ref name=":9">{{Cite web|title=Anti-coup mass protests take place in cities across Myanmar|url=https://www.myanmar-now.org/en/news/anti-coup-mass-protests-take-place-in-cities-across-myanmar|access-date=2021-02-07|website=Myanmar NOW|language=en}}</ref> မၞိဟ်ထ္ၜးဆန္ဒတအ် အာတ်မိက် ညံင်ဂွံဗလးကဵု ဒဝ်အံင်သာန်သုကျဳ ကေုာံ ဦးဝေန်မျေအ်၊ ကရေဲဒၟံင် "ပၟိက်ပိုယ် (ဒို့အရေး) ကေုာံ တၠအဝဵုပၞာန် ကဵုကျညိ။<ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=|title=စစ်အာဏာသိမ်းဆန့်ကျင်မှု ဒုတိယနေ့လူထုဆန္ဒပြပွဲများ|url=https://burmese.voanews.com/a/myanmar-military-coup-protest/5768491.html|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2021-02-07|website=ဗွီအိုအေ|language=my}}</ref> ပ္ဍဲတ္ၚဲဂှ် ဍုင်သကုတ်လတူမ္ဂး နေပျဳဒဝ်၊ မာန္တလေ၊ ဗုကာံ၊ ဖာက၊ လာရှဝ်၊ မကွေ၊ ပျေဥူလွန်၊ တံင်ကျဳ၊ ဍုင်ဗၟာသကုတ်သၟဝ်မ္ဂး မတ်မလီု၊ ထဝါဲ၊ ဖာသီ၊ မြံင်မြ၊ ဗြဝတဳ။<ref name=":9" /><ref>{{Cite web|date=2021-02-07|title=Tens of Thousands Take to Streets in Myanmar to Protest Military Regime|url=https://www.irrawaddy.com/news/burma/tens-thousands-take-streets-myanmar-protest-military-regime.html|access-date=2021-02-07|website=The Irrawaddy|language=en-US}}</ref><ref name=":10" />
[[File:Protesters riding Motorcycles in Mandalay after 2021 Myanmar coup.jpg|thumb|Protesters riding motorcycles on [[78th Road]] near [[Mandalay Central Railway Station]]]]

ပ္ဍဲ ၈ ဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ဂှ် ညးထ္ၜးဆန္ဒတအ် ဆက်ကၠောန်ဒၟံင်ရ။ ပ္ဍဲကဵုဍုင်ဇၞော် နေပဳတဝ်ဂှ် ဗၠာဲသၟိင်တအ် ဒးစကာပါက်ဍာ် သွက်ဂွံပရးမၞိဟ်။<ref>{{Cite web|title=Myanmar police fire water cannon in Naypyidaw, warn protesters to disperse or face force|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/myanmar-protest-police-water-cannon-naypyidaw-14137604|access-date=2021-02-08|website=CNA|language=en}}</ref> တဳဝဳဍုင်ဗၟာ MRTV လလောင်တြး ကမၠောန်ဒစဵုဒစး သၟိင်တၠအဝဵုတအ်ဂှ် ဒှ်ကမၠောန်မ္ၚးသၞောဝ်။<ref>{{Cite web|title=Martial law declared in parts of Myanmar as rallies heap pressure on coup leaders|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/martial-law-parts-myanmar-protests-military-coup-mandalay-14140170|access-date=2021-02-08|website=CNA|language=en}}</ref> ကုညးမကၠောန် ကမၠောန်မဗၠေတ်သၞောဝ်တအ်ဂှ် ရန်ဂီုကၠီုဍုင် သၞောဝ်တန်ကြန်ဍုင်တုဲ သရပ်စပ်အာ အတိုင်သၞောဝ်ရောင်ဂှ် နူကဵုတဳဝဳဂှ် လလောင်တြးလဝ်ရ။<ref>{{Cite news|date=2021-02-08|title=Myanmar state TV says public does not accept wrongdoers, warns of legal action|language=en|work=Reuters|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-politics-statetv-idUSKBN2A80RY|url-status=live|access-date=2021-02-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=2021-02-09|title=ပြည်သူသို့ မေတ္တာရပ်ခံချက်|url=https://www.facebook.com/mrtvwebmediaportal/posts/3858998297479301|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=|website=MRTV|language=my}}</ref> သဝ်တ္ၚဲဂှ် နကဵုဍုင် ပ္တိတ်သၞောဝ်ပၞာန် (martial law) တုဲ ဟွံကဵုအခေါင်အာကၠုင် ပ္ဍဲအခိင်ဗတံ။

ပ္ဍဲ ၉ ဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ညးထ္ၜးဆန္ဒတုဲ ဟွံဒ္ဂေတ်ဗက် သၞောဝ်ပၞာန် ဆက်တိတ် ထ္ၜးဆန္ဒ ဒၞာဲဗွဲမဂၠိုင်ရ။<ref>{{Cite web|date=2021-02-08|title=Myanmar junta imposes curfew, meeting bans as protests swell|url=https://apnews.com/article/myanmar-anti-coup-protest-fd4252fbd800caa5d457de9dd65293b7|access-date=2021-02-09|website=AP NEWS}}</ref> ဗၠာဲသၟိင်တအ် ပရးမၞိဟ် နကဵုမပန်ကဵု မကမ်ရဝ်ဗါ၊ စကာ ပါက်ဍာ်။<ref name=":27">{{Cite web|date=2021-02-09|title=Myanmar junta cracks down on crowds defying protest ban|url=https://apnews.com/article/myanmar-junta-cracks-down-protests-62f96ec2e545d4bcbf86392c070d9a44|access-date=2021-02-09|website=AP NEWS}}</ref> မၞိဟ်မဒးဝပ် ဒးဘဲဗွဲမဂၠိုင် ရုင်ကုလသမဂ္ဂ ပ္ဍဲဍုင်ဗၟာ ပ္တိတ်လိက်လလောင်တြး အာတ်မိက် ပွမလၞိန်ဗပိန် ညးထ္ၜးဆန္ဒဗီုဗီုဏအ် ဟွံဒုင်တဲရ။<ref name=":27" />
[[File:Protesters cosplay Lady Justice in Yangon (11 February 2021).jpg|alt=protesters cosplay lady justice|thumb|Protesters cosplay Lady Justice in Yangon (11 February 2021)]]
ရုင်ဗၠာဲသၟိင် ပ္ဍဲကဵုဍုင်ဇၞော်ဇၞော် ဗီုကဵု နေပျဳတစ် ကေုာံ မကွေတအ်ဂှ် ဒးဒုင်ကၠဟ်ပလီု နကဵု ညးထ္ၜးဆန္ဒတအ်။<ref>{{Cite web|title=Handful of police officers join Myanmar's uprising against military regime|url=https://www.myanmar-now.org/en/news/handful-of-police-officers-join-myanmars-uprising-against-military-regime|access-date=2021-02-09|website=Myanmar NOW|language=en}}</ref> ပ္ဍဲ ၉ ဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ဗၠာဲသၟိင် ခွန်အောင်ကိုကို နူကဵု ရုင်ဗၠာဲသၟိင် နေပျဳတဝ် တိတ်နူလျိုင်တုဲ လုပ်ပံင်ကဵု ညးထ္ၜးဆန္ဒတအ်၊ ညးဂှ် ဒှ်ဗၠာဲသၟိင် အဃောမယိုက်ဂၠေင်တာလျိုင် တိတ်ပံင်တောဲ ကုညးထ္ၜးဆန္ဒ ကိုပ်ကၠာအိုတ်ရ။<ref name=":30">{{Cite web|title=Across Myanmar, police set their fears aside to show solidarity with fellow citizens|url=https://www.myanmar-now.org/en/news/across-myanmar-police-set-their-fears-aside-to-show-solidarity-with-fellow-citizens|access-date=2021-02-11|website=Myanmar NOW|language=en}}</ref> ပ္ဍဲဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ၁၀ ဂကောံဗၠာဲသၟိင် မွဲဂကောံ နူကဵုတွဵုရးဍုင်ကရေင် လလောင်တြး ဟွံထံက်ဂလာန် ပၞာန်သီအဝဵု။<ref>{{Cite web|date=2021-02-11|title=In rural Myanmar, residents protect police who reject coup|url=https://apnews.com/article/world-news-race-and-ethnicity-myanmar-63165d7894a4ab97a20ab24be592626d|access-date=2021-02-11|website=AP NEWS}}</ref>

ပ္ဍဲဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ၁၁၊ ၂၀၂၁ ဂှ် ကောန်မန်၊ ကရေင်၊ ပအိုအ်တအ် ပံင်ကောံတုဲ ထ္ၜးဆန္ဒ ပ္ဍဲလတူဍုင်မတ်မလီု နကဵုတင်ရန်တၟအ် "တၠအဝဵုလဵုဟွံဟီု ဒစဵုဒစးဖအိုတ် (အာဏာရှင်ဟူသမျှ တော်လှန်ကျ)"။ ရမ္သာင်ကရေဲ အဓိကဂှ် ပန်တင် " အာဏာရှင်စနစ် တိုက်ဖျက်ရေး ဒို့အရေး၊ ၂၀၀၈ ဖွဲ့စည်းပုံအခြေခံဥပဒေ ဖျက်သိမ်းရေး ဒို့အရေး၊ ဖက်ဒရယ်ဒီမိုကရေစီ ပြည်ထောင်စု ပေါ်ပေါက်ရေး ဒို့အရေး၊ မတရား ဖမ်းဆီးထိန်းသိမ်းခံရသူများ လွှတ်ပေးရေး ဒို့အရေး" ပ္ဍဲဂှ် သၟတ်မန်မွဲ ဟီုကဵု အစာပရိုင်ဌာန်ဗၠးၜးမန် "ပိုယ်ဂှ် တၠအဝဵုပၞာန်လေဝ် ဟွံမဲပၟိက်၊ တၠအဝဵုဒဳမဝ်ကရေသဳလေဝ် ဟွံမဲပၟိက်၊ တၠအဝဵု ဂကူလဵုလေဝ် ဟွံမဲပၟိက်၊ ဟိုတ်ဂှ်ရ ပိုယ်ထ္ၜးဆန္ဒ နကဵုက္ဍိုပ် တၠအဝဵုလဵုဟွံဟီု ပိုယ်ဒစဵုဒစးဖအိုတ်"။ ညံင်ရဴ ပ္ဍဲဍုင်မတ်မလီုကီု ပ္ဍဲဍုင်လ္ဂုင်လေဝ် ကောန်ဍုင်အရင် မပ္တံကဵု ဂကူကရေင်၊ ဂကူကချေင်၊ ဂကူချေင်၊ ဂကူမန်၊ ဂကူသေံ၊ ဂကူယခေင်၊ ဂကူဗမာ၊ ဂကူလဳသူ၊ ဂကူဝ၊ ဂကူပအိုအ်၊ ဂကူပလံင်၊ ဂကူဒိုင်နက်၊ ဂကူမြို့၊ ဂကူအင်းသား၊ ဂကူမရမာကြီး၊ ဂကူသက်၊ ဂကူဟိန္ဒူ၊ တမေလ်တအ် ပံင်ကောံတုဲ ထ္ၜးဆန္ဒ မအာတ်မိက် သၞောတ်ဖေက်ဒရေဝ်ကီုရ။ <ref>{{Cite web|date=2021-02-11|title=အာဏာရှင်ဟူသမျှ တော်လှန်သော တိုင်းရင်းသားလူငယ်များ မော်လမြိုင်မြို့တွင် ဆန္ဒထုတ်ဖော်|url=http://burmese.monnews.org/2021/02/11/အာဏာရှင်ဟူသမျှ-တော်လှန်/?fbclid=IwAR1n1fhkJwglY1NY5w3S_0odA0a-SlHItYdffvu9Boq0QMZpsoa26vSkvNw|access-date=2021-02-13|website=Mon News Agency}}</ref>

ပ္ဍဲ ၁၂ ဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ မဒှ် တ္ၚဲကၟိန်ဍုင်ပံင်ကောံဂှ် ဗၠာဲသၟိင်တအ် အာတ်မိက် ကဵုပရးမၞိဟ်တုဲ ဟိုတ်နူ ဟွံပရးတုဲ ဗၠာဲသၟိင် လုပ်ထကးမၞိဟ်အတေင်၊ ပန်ဘပဠဂၠံင်လတူ၊ မၞိဟ်ဒစိတ်တၠ ဒးဒုင်ရပ် ပ္ဍဲမတ်မလီု။<ref>{{Cite web|date=2021-02-12|title=Myanmar protests: shots heard in southeast city as police disperse crowd|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/asia/southeast-asia/article/3121563/myanmar-military-pardons-23000-prisoners-protests-rage|access-date=2021-02-12|website=South China Morning Post|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Limited|first=Bangkok Post Public Company|title=Protesters defy Myanmar junta, shots fired in Mawlamyine|work=Bangkok Post|url=https://www.bangkokpost.com/world/2067231/protesters-defy-myanmar-junta-shots-fired-in-mawlamyine|access-date=2021-02-12}}</ref> ကြဴနူ မရပ်ကြိုင်လဝ် ပွိုင် ၈ နာဍဳတုဲ ကလေင်ဗလးကဵု သီုညးဖအိုတ်ပၠန်။<ref>{{Cite news|last=News|first=7Day|title=မော်လမြိုင်တွင်ဆန္ဒပြရာမှ ကျောင်းသားအချို့အပါအဝင် ကိုးဦးအား ဖမ်းဆီးပြီးနောက် ပြန်လွှတ်ပေ|work=7Day News|url=https://7day.news/detail?id=303590|access-date=2021-02-13|website=7Day News|language=Burmese}}</ref>

=== မစၟတ်သမ္တီ သွဟ်မာဲ ===
မၞိဟ်စၞးမဂွံဇမၞးလဝ်မာဲ နူကဵု သဘင်မာဲ နဝ်ဝေမ်ဗါ ၂၀၂၀ ဂှ် နကဵု အလဵုအသဳပၞာန် ဟွံပဒတန် လုပ်သၞောဝ်ဏီရ။ ပ္ဍဲဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ၄၊ ၂၀၂၁ ဂှ် မၞိဟ်စၞး နူကဵု ဗော်အေန်အေဝ်ဒဳ ၜိုတ် ၇၀ တၠ ကၠောန်သဘင်ဒုင်သစာ ပ္ဍဲနေပျဳတဝ်၊ တုဲ လလောင်တြး ဇကုဂှ် ဒှ်မၞိဟ်စၞး ညးဍုင်ကွာန် မရုဲစှ်လဝ် နဒဒှ် မၞိဟ်မဂွံအခေါင်ပတန်သၞောဝ် ပွိုင်အာယုက် မသုန်သၞာံရ။<ref>{{cite web|date=2021-02-04|title=NLD lawmakers in Nay Pyi Taw defy military, take oath of office |url=https://www.frontiermyanmar.net/en/nld-lawmakers-in-nay-pyi-taw-defy-military-take-oath-of-office/|access-date=2021-02-06|publisher=Frontier Myanmar}}</ref> တ္ၚဲယးဂှ် မၞိဟ်စၞး ၃၀၀ တၠ ပဒတန် ဒဒှ်ရ ညးတအ် ဒက်ပ္တန်လဝ် ကမ္မတဳမပစၞးစၠတ်ထဝ်ကၟိန်ဍုင်။<ref name=":16">{{Cite web|date=2021-02-08|title=Amid Coup, Myanmar's NLD Lawmakers Form Committee to Serve as Legitimate Parliament|url=https://www.irrawaddy.com/news/burma/amid-coup-myanmars-nld-lawmakers-form-committee-serve-legitimate-parliament.html|access-date=2021-02-08|website=The Irrawaddy|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|date=2021-02-05|title=Myanmar politicians defy coup, say they are true government|url=https://apnews.com/article/myanmar-coup-politicians-a576dcd73070070877e8d567ec5e8a5c|access-date=2021-02-06|agency=AP NEWS}}</ref> နကဵု ကမ္မတဳဂှ် ကၠောန်သဘင်ကောံဓရီုကိုပ်ကၠာအိုတ် နကဵု [[Zoom (software)|Zoom]]။<ref>{{Cite news|date=2021-02-08|title=After a decade of change in Myanmar, fear of the past drives anti-coup protests|language=en|work=Reuters|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-politics-past-idUSKBN2A70HI|url-status=live|access-date=2021-02-08}}</ref>

ပ္ဍဲ ၆ ဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ၂၀၂၁ ဗော်ပရေင်ဍုင်ကွာန် ဗွဲမဂၠိုင် သီုကဵု ဗော်ကောန်ဂကူသေံ (Shan Nationalities League for Democracy SNLD)၊ ဗော် (Democratic Party for a New Society)၊ ဗော်ကောန်ဂကူကရေင် (Karen National Party) ကေုာံ ဗော်ကောန်ဂကူချေင်အရှဝ် (Asho Chin National Party) လလောင်တြး ဒဒှ်ရ ဒပ်ပၞာန် အာတ်မိက် ညံင်ဗော်ညးတအ် ဂွံပလံင်မၞိဟ်စၞး ပ္ဍဲကံင်သဳစၟိန်ပြမာန်ဍုင်ဂှ် ညးတအ် ဟွံဒုင်တဲ။<ref name=":5">{{cite web|title=SNLD, DPNS reject offer to participate in new government|url=https://elevenmyanmar.com/news/snld-dpns-reject-offer-to-participate-in-new-government|access-date=2021-02-06 |newspaper=Eleven Media Group Co., Ltd}}</ref> နကဵုဗော်ဇၞော်မောဝ်ကရေင်ဍာဲ (Karenni National Progressive Party) လလောင်တြး ဒစဵုဒစး ပၞာန်သီအဝဵု အာတ်မိက် ဂွံပသောင်ပြသၞာဍုင် နကဵုနဲမဆဵုဂဗတက်ကျာ။<ref>{{Cite web|date=2021-02-08|title=Karenni National Progressive Party urges NLD and Tatmadaw to negotiate|url=https://www.mmtimes.com/news/karenni-national-progressive-party-urges-nld-and-tatmadaw-negotiate.html|access-date=2021-02-08|website=The Myanmar Times}}</ref>

ပ္ဍဲ ၇ ဖေဖဝ်ဝါရဳ ကမ္မတဳပါလဳမာန်ဂှ် လလောင်တြး ဒဒှ်ရ ပၞာန်သီအဝဵုဂှ် ဒှ်အရာမကလိလောန်ဒုဟ် တုဲပၠန် ကပိနေတ်ဝန်ဇၞော် မင်းအောင်လှိုင် မဒက်လဝ်ဂှ် ဒှ်အရာ မဟွံလုပ်ကဵုသၞောဝ်။<ref name=":16" /> နကဵု ကမ္မတဳဂှ်ဟီု ပၞာန်ကလိလောန်ဒုဟ် အတိုင်သၞောဝ်ပိုဒ် ၆တုဲ ဟီု ညံင်အဝဵုဍုင်ဂှ် ကလေင်ပအပ်ကဵု အလဵုအသဳညးဍုင်ကွာန်။<ref name=":16" /> နကဵုကမ္မတဳဂှ် ကဵုကသပ် ကုကုလသမဂ္ဂ ကေုာံ ဍုင်နာနာ ကိစ္စဍုင်ဗၟာ အရာအိုတ်သီုဂှ် ဒးဆက်ကဵုညးတအ်။<ref name=":16" />

==ဗီုအလဵုအသဳပၞာန် မရပ်စပ်ဂမၠိုင်==
=== ထပိုတ်အေန်တာနေတ် ===
On 4 February 2021, telecom operators and internet providers across Myanmar were ordered to block [[Facebook]] until 7 February 2021, to ensure the "country's stability".<ref name=":15">{{cite news|date=2021-02-03|title=Myanmar internet providers block Facebook services after government order|agency=Reuters|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-politics-facebook-idUSKBN2A32ZE|url-status=live|access-date=2021-02-04}}</ref> [[Myanma Posts and Telecommunications]] (MPT), a state-owned carrier, also blocked [[Facebook Messenger]], [[Instagram]] and [[WhatsApp]] services, while [[Telenor Myanmar]] blocked only Facebook.<ref>{{cite web|date=2021-02-03|title=Directive to block social media service|url=https://www.telenor.com/directive-to-block-social-media-service/|access-date=2021-02-04|publisher=Telenor Group}}</ref><ref name=":15"/> Facebook had been used to organize the civil disobedience campaign's labour strikes and the emerging boycott movement.<ref name=":15"/> Facebook is used by half of Myanmar's population.<ref name=":15"/> Following the Facebook ban, Burmese users had begun flocking to Twitter.<ref name=":7">{{cite news|last=Potkin|first=Fanny|date=2021-02-05|title=After Facebook ban, thousands in Myanmar take to Twitter to plead #RespectOurVotes|agency=Reuters|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-politics-twitter-idUSKBN2A5189|access-date=2021-02-06}}</ref> The following day, the government extended the social media access ban to include Instagram and [[Twitter]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Myanmar's new military government is now blocking Twitter and Instagram|url=https://social.techcrunch.com/2021/02/05/myanmar-military-government-is-now-blocking-twitter/|access-date=2021-02-06|publisher=TechCrunch}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|date=2021-02-05|title=Directive to block social media services Twitter and Instagram in Myanmar |url=https://www.telenor.com/directive-to-block-social-media-services-twitter-and-instagram-in-myanmar/|access-date=2021-02-06|publisher=Telenor Group}}</ref> On the morning of 6 February 2021, the military authorities initiated an [[internet outage]] nationwide.<ref>{{cite web|date=2021-02-06|title=Myanmar junta blocks internet access as coup protests expand|url=https://apnews.com/article/united-nations-myanmar-media-social-media-yangon-e7765d3459d386219ee1dca8ad1e089c|access-date=2021-02-06|agency=AP NEWS}}</ref> That same day, Facebook urged authorities to unblock social media services.<ref>{{cite news|date=2021-02-06|title=Facebook urges unblocking of Myanmar social media|agency=Reuters|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-politics-facebook-idUSKBN2A60DE|access-date=2021-02-07}}</ref> Internet access was partially restored the following day, although social media platforms remained blocked.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Internet access partially restored in Myanmar as protests grow against military coup|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/internet-access-partially-restored-in-myanmar-as-protests-grow-14131802|access-date=2021-02-07|website=CNA|language=en}}</ref>

=== Proposed cybersecurity law ===
On 9 February, a 36-page draft [[Computer security|cybersecurity]] law was circulated to Myanmar's mobile operators and telecoms license holders for industry feedback.<ref name=":31">{{Cite news|title=Myanmar junta cyber bill would violate rights, critics say|work=Reuters|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/myanmar-politics-internet-int-idUSKBN2AA2AU|access-date=2021-02-11}}</ref> The draft bill would make internet providers accountable for preventing or removing content that "cause[s] hatred, destroy unity and tranquility."<ref name=":31" /> A coalition of 150 civil service organisations publicly denounced the bill for violating the fundamental rights to [[Freedom of speech|freedom of expression]], [[Information privacy|data protection]], and privacy, and other democratic norms in the digital space, and for granting state authorities the ability to ban unfavorable content, restrict ISPs, and intercept data.<ref name=":31" />

On 11 February, hundreds of protesters gathered at the Embassy of China in Yangon, based on online rumours that China had brought in telecommunications equipment and IT experts to Myanmar via recent flights.<ref name=":32">{{Cite news|last=Staff|first=Reuters|date=2021-02-11|title=Myanmar anti-coup protesters rally at Chinese embassy|language=en|work=Reuters|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/myanmar-politics-china-int-idUSKBN2AB0HE|access-date=2021-02-11}}</ref> The Chinese embassy attempted to dismiss the rumours on Facebook by publishing a statement from the China Enterprises Chamber of Commerce in Myanmar which claimed that recent cargo flights had only transported goods like seafood.<ref name=":32" /><ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=2021-02-11|title=关于中缅货运航班的情况说明|url=https://www.facebook.com/paukphawfriendship/photos/a.192320247510703/3681368825272477/|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=|website=缅甸中国企业商会|language=zh}}</ref>

=== Media blackout ===
[[File:During Internet shutdown, one of the electronic shop sales the portable radio in Yangon, Myanmar.jpg|thumb|During the ongoing internet and media blackout, many have switched to radio to obtain news. A handwritten Burmese sign reads "Radios are now available," with the acronyms of several major international radio news stations, including BBC, VOA, and RFA.]]
Since the coup on 1 February, authorities have blocked popular news channels, including free-to-air channels like the [[Democratic Voice of Burma]] and [[Mizzima TV]], as well as foreign news channels, including CNN, NHK, and BBC.<ref name=":20" /><ref name=":17">{{Cite web|date=2021-02-08|title=US Ambassador Calls for Myanmar Military to Restore Power to Elected Government|url=https://www.irrawaddy.com/news/burma/us-ambassador-calls-myanmar-military-restore-power-elected-government.html|access-date=2021-02-08|website=The Irrawaddy|language=en-US}}</ref> On 7 February, the regime also blocked the [[The New York Times|New York Times]], [[The Wall Street Journal|Wall Street Journal]], [[The Economist]] and two wire services, the [[Associated Press]] and [[Reuters]].<ref name=":17" /> A [[Myanmar Press Council]] representative has expressed concern over the future of [[freedom of the press]] in the country, the public's right to access information, and the future of Myanmar's nascent news organisations.<ref name=":20" />

=== Arrests and charges ===
Law enforcement authorities have acted swiftly in quelling opposition to the coup. As of 7 February 2021, 152 people were under detention in relation to the coup d'état.<ref name=":1"/>

The military regime has begun initiating criminal proceedings against detainees. On 3 February 2021, Thawbita, a Buddhist monk was sentenced to 2 years in prison under Section 66(d) of the Telecommunications Law, for defamation of the military.<ref>{{cite web|date=2021-02-04|title=Statement on Recent Detainees in Relation to the Military Coup|url=https://aappb.org/2021/02/statement-on-recent-detainees-in-relation-to-the-military-coup/|access-date=2021-02-06|website=aappb.org {{!}} Assistance Association for Political Prisoners}}</ref> On 4 February 2021, three university students, Zu Zu Zan, Aung Myo Ko, and Htoo Khant Thaw, were charged under Section 19 of the Peaceful Assembly and Peaceful Procession Law for protesting in Mandalay.<ref name=":1"/> On 5 February 2021, Maung Gyi, chair of the United Nationalities Democratic Party, was arrested, charged and sentenced to two years under Penal Code Section 505(b) for staging a protest in [[Hpa-an Township]], [[Kayin State]].<ref name=":1"/> Cho Yu Mon, a school principal, was also arrested and charged under Penal Code Section 505(b) for taking part in a "red ribbon" campaign at her school in Hpa-an.<ref name=":2">{{cite web|date=2021-02-05|title=Statement on Recent Detainees in Relation to the Military Coup News Updated on 5 February 2021|url=https://aappb.org/2021/02/statement-on-recent-detainees-in-relation-to-the-military-coup-news-updated-on-5-feb-2021/|access-date=2021-02-06 |website=aappb.org {{!}} Assistance Association for Political Prisoners}}</ref> NLD leader [[Win Htein]] was charged under Section 124(a) of Myanmar's legal code for [[sedition]].<ref name=":2"/> 

On 6 February, Sean Turnell, the Australian economic policy advisor to the NLD-led civilian government and a [[Macquarie University]] professor, was detained, becoming the first known foreign national to be arrested in relation to the coup.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Myanmar detains Australian adviser to Aung San Suu Kyi; first known arrest of foreign national since coup|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/myanmar-coup-australian-adviser-aung-san-suu-kyi-detained-14126558|access-date=2021-02-07|website=CNA|language=en}}</ref>

On 8 February, authorities re-arrested [[Nang Khin Htwe Myint]], Kayin State's chief minister, and [[Myint Naing]], Sagaing Region's chief minister.<ref name=":18">{{Cite web|date=2021-02-08|title=Myanmar’s Military Re-Arrests Two Chief Ministers|url=https://www.irrawaddy.com/news/burma/myanmars-military-re-arrests-two-chief-ministers.html|access-date=2021-02-08|website=The Irrawaddy|language=en-US}}</ref> Nang Khin Htwe Myint had published remarks online urging solidarity between soldiers and the people, pointing out that the army was funded by taxes and state funds, while Myint Naing had posted a speech calling on the public to continue protesting.<ref name=":18" />

On 9 February, at least 100 demonstrators were arrested in Mandalay, including vice-mayor [[Ye Lwin]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=2021-02-09|title=Protest crackdown begins in Myanmar, over 100 nabbed in Mandalay|url=https://www.mmtimes.com/news/protest-crackdown-begins-myanmar-over-100-nabbed-mandalay.html|access-date=2021-02-09|website=The Myanmar Times}}</ref>

=== Inclusion of opposition political parties ===
The military has made overtures to competing political parties in the aftermath of the coup d'état.<ref name=":5"/> On 2 February 2021, it formed the [[State Administration Council]], as Myanmar's interim governing body. The Council's membership included several civilian politicians, including [[Mahn Nyein Maung]], a former member of the [[Karen National Union]], [[Thein Nyunt (politician)|Thein Nyunt]], and [[Khin Maung Swe]], co-founders of the [[National Democratic Force]], a splinter group from the NLD.<ref>{{cite web|title=မန်းငြိမ်းမောင်၊ ဦးသိန်းညွန့်နဲ့ ဦးခင်မောင်ဆွေတို့ကို တပ်မတော်နေရာပေး |url=https://www.rfa.org/burmese/news/military-coup-myanmar-new-government-02022021114403.html|access-date=2 February 2021|publisher=Radio Free Asia|language=my}}</ref> On 3 February 2021, five additional civilian members were added to the Council, including [[Aye Nu Sein]], vice-chair of the [[Arakan National Party]].<ref name=":5"/><ref name=":14">{{cite web|title=ပြည်ထောင်စုသမ္မတမြန်မာနိုင်ငံတော် နိုင်ငံတော်စီမံအုပ်ချုပ်ရေးကောင်စီ အမိန့်အမှတ် ( ၁၄ / ၂၀၂၁) ၁၃၈၂ ခုနှစ်၊ ပြာသိုလပြည့်ကျော် ၇ ရက် ၂၀၂၁ ခုနှစ်၊ ဖေဖော်ဝါရီလ ၃ ရက်|url=http://www.dsinfo.org/node/973|access-date=4 February 2021|publisher=Tatmadaw Information Team|language=my}}</ref> On 6 February, the [[Mon Unity Party]] had announced it had accepted the military's offer to join the Council.<ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=|title=အုပ်ချုပ်ရေးကောင်စီမှာ ပါဝင်ဖို့ စစ်အစိုးရကမ်းလှမ်းချက် မွန်ညီညွတ်ရေးပါတီ လက်ခံ|url=https://www.rfa.org/burmese/news/mup-accept-coup-council-02062021134515.html|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2021-02-07|website=Radio Free Asia|language=my}}</ref>

=== Spread of misinformation ===
The internet blackout has fueled the spread of [[misinformation]], including unsubstantiated rumours of Suu Kyi's release, the death of high-profile NLD leaders, and the fall of Min Aung Hlaing.<ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=|title=ဒေါ်အောင်ဆန်းစုကြည် လွတ်ပြီဆိုသည့်သတင်းမှား ပျံ့နှံ့နေ|url=https://www.rfa.org/burmese/news/dassk-release-rumor-02062021113852.html|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2021-02-07|website=Radio Free Asia|language=my}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|date=2021-02-07|title=After a decade of change in Myanmar, fear of the past drives anti-coup protests|language=en|work=Reuters|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-politics-past-idUSKBN2A70HI|url-status=live|access-date=2021-02-07}}</ref> The rumour surrounding Suu Kyi's release, which was attributed to the military-run [[Myawaddy TV]], triggered street celebrations and fireworks.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Myanmar coup: Tens of thousands protest and call for Aung San Suu Kyi's release despite internet being cut off|url=https://news.sky.com/story/myanmar-coup-tens-of-thousands-protest-and-call-for-aung-san-suu-kyis-release-despite-internet-being-cut-off-12211146|access-date=2021-02-07|website=Sky News|language=en}}</ref>

=== Imposition of martial law ===
On 8 February, authorities began imposing [[martial law]] across several municipalities until further notice.<ref name=":19">{{Cite web|date=2021-02-08|title=Myanmar junta promises multiparty election, family of detained Australian call for his release|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2021-02-09/martial-law-declared-in-seven-myanmar-townships/13133906|access-date=2021-02-08|website=www.abc.net.au|language=en-AU}}</ref> Martial law effectively institutes a nightly curfew from 8 pm to 4 am, bans gathering of more than 5 individuals,<ref name=":24">{{Cite web|date=2021-02-08|title=UPDATED Curfews imposed in townships across Myanmar amid widespread protests|url=https://www.mmtimes.com/news/updated-curfews-imposed-townships-across-myanmar-amid-widespread-protests.html|access-date=2021-02-08|website=The Myanmar Times}}</ref> public speaking, rallies, and protests.<ref name=":19" /> Municipalities covered by martial law include 7 townships in Mandalay, and a township in Ayeyarwady Region.<ref name=":19" /> Martial law has since been expanded to include several urban townships in Yangon, Shwebo, Monywa, Sagaing, Kalay in Sagaing Region, Bago, and Pharsong in Kayah State, where significant protests had emerged.<ref name=":24" /> Martial law has since been expanded to include 90 townships in 30 cities, including all the townships that comprise Yangon.<ref>{{Cite web|date=2021-02-09|title=90 townships in 30 cities across Myanmar under curfew order|url=https://www.mmtimes.com/news/90-townships-30-cities-across-myanmar-under-curfew-order.html|access-date=2021-02-09|website=The Myanmar Times}}</ref>

=== Pro-military counter-protests ===
In the lead-up to the coup, pro-military protesters had begun rallying in an attempt to delegitimise the results of the 2020 elections.<ref name=":25">{{Cite web|title=Pro-military protesters hurl bricks at police car while rallying against the Union Election Commission|url=https://www.myanmar-now.org/en/news/pro-military-protesters-hurl-bricks-at-police-car-while-rallying-against-the-union-election|access-date=2021-02-08|website=Myanmar NOW|language=en}}</ref> [[Wai Wai Nu]] of the Women's Peace Network noted the potential for violent attacks on pro-democracy protesters by pro-military protesters.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Kirby|first=Jen|date=2021-02-08|title=Tens of thousands rise up against the coup in Myanmar|url=https://www.vox.com/2021/2/8/22272367/myanmar-protests-coup-democracy|access-date=2021-02-08|website=Vox|language=en}}</ref> On 30 December, approximately 400 pro-military protesters and nationalists demonstrated in front of [[Yangon City Hall]], in violation of COVID-19 guidelines.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Hundreds attend pro-military protest in defiance of Covid-19 restrictions|url=https://www.myanmar-now.org/en/news/hundreds-attend-pro-military-protest-in-defiance-of-covid-19-restrictions|access-date=2021-02-08|website=Myanmar NOW|language=en}}</ref> On 14 January, about a thousand protesters gathered in Mandalay's [[Pyawbwe Township]] to dispute election results, waving flags with army insignia.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Over a thousand protesters defy ban on large gatherings, army-related slogans at Mandalay rally|url=https://www.myanmar-now.org/en/news/over-a-thousand-protesters-defy-ban-on-large-gatherings-army-related-slogans-at-mandalay-rally|access-date=2021-02-08|website=Myanmar NOW|language=en}}</ref> 

On 28 January, pro-military protesters incited violence, hurling bricks at a police car in Yangon.<ref name=":25" /> None of the protesters were arrested, and were then transported away from the site by 10 unmarked vehicles.<ref name=":25" /> On the evening of 30 January, approximately 500 pro-military protesters incited a riot near Yangon's Shwedagon Pagoda.<ref>{{Cite web|date=2021-01-31|title=Pro-Tatmadaw protesters spark riot in Yangon|url=https://www.mmtimes.com/news/pro-tatmadaw-protesters-spark-riot-yangon.html|access-date=2021-02-08|website=The Myanmar Times}}</ref> On 2 February, the day after the coup, pro-military protesters and Burmese nationalists rallied in Yangon.<ref>{{Cite news|date=2021-02-02|title=Myanmar Army Rallies Supporters, Bans Flights Through April|language=en|work=Bloomberg.com|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2021-02-02/myanmar-army-rallies-supporters-bans-flights-through-april|access-date=2021-02-08}}</ref> On 8 February, a group of pro-military protesters rallied at Sule Pagoda.<ref>{{Cite web|date=2021-02-08|title=MYANMAR PROTESTS LIVE: Tens of thousands gathering in Yangon, demonstrations in other major cities|url=https://www.frontiermyanmar.net/en/myanmar-protests-live-tens-of-thousands-gathering-in-yangon-demonstrations-in-other-major-cities/|access-date=2021-02-08|website=Frontier Myanmar|language=en-US}}</ref>

On 9 February, a group of pro-military instigators arrived at a protest site in Yangon in 15 unmarked vehicles, seeking to provoke violence.<ref name=":28">{{Cite web|title=Pro-military groups tried to disrupt anti-coup protests|url=https://www.myanmar-now.org/en/news/pro-military-groups-tried-to-disrupt-anti-coup-protests|access-date=2021-02-10|website=Myanmar NOW|language=en}}</ref> Many brandished large wooden clubs, and were otherwise indistinguishable from pro-democracy protesters.<ref name=":28" />

=== Excessive use of force ===
On 8 February, police began using [[rubber bullets]], [[live ammunition]], [[water cannon]]s, and [[tear gas]] to disperse protesters at mass rallies.<ref>{{Cite news|date=2021-02-09|title=Myanmar coup: Police fire rubber bullets as protesters defy ban|language=en-GB|work=BBC News|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-55991210|access-date=2021-02-09}}</ref> The military leader [[Min Aung Hlaing]] ordered a clampdown and suppression of demonstrations as protesters nationwide embarked on a strike. On 9 February, 2 protesters in Naypyidaw were admitted to a local hospital in critical condition, for gunshot wounds.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Two people in critical condition after police shoot peaceful protesters with live bullets in Naypyitaw - doctor|url=https://www.myanmar-now.org/en/news/two-people-in-critical-condition-after-police-shoot-peaceful-protesters-with-live-bullets-in|access-date=2021-02-09|website=Myanmar NOW|language=en}}</ref> A 19-year-old woman, Mya Thwe Thwe Khaing,<ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=2021-02-10|title=မမြသွဲ့သွဲ့ခိုင် ပစ်ခတ်ခံရမှုအပေါ် UN အထူးကိုယ်စားလှယ် မေးခွန်းထုတ်|url=https://burma.irrawaddy.com/news/2021/02/10/237873.html|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2021-02-10|website=ဧရာဝတီ|language=my}}</ref> was pronounced [[Brain death|brain dead]],<ref>{{Cite web|date=2021-02-10|title=Election 2020 {{!}} Family of Police Crackdown’s Victim Urges Rooting Out Dictatorship|url=https://www.irrawaddy.com/elections/family-police-crackdowns-victim-urges-rooting-dictatorship.html|access-date=2021-02-10|website=The Irrawaddy|language=en-US}}</ref> and placed on life support after being shot in the head with live ammunition<ref>{{Cite news|date=2021-02-10|title=‘It was her spirit’: Myanmar teen shot by police was determined to protest coup|language=en|work=Reuters|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/myanmar-politics-victim-int-idUSKBN2AA1J8|url-status=live|access-date=2021-02-11}}</ref> by police.<ref name="guardian/woman shot in head">{{cite news|date=9 February 2021|title=Myanmar protests: woman shot in head as police response escalates|language=en|work=the Guardian|url=https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2021/feb/09/myanmar-protesters-curfew-junta-demonstrators-army|access-date=10 February 2021}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Girl shot by police in Naypyitaw crackdown put on life support: doctor|url=https://www.myanmar-now.org/en/news/girl-shot-by-police-in-naypyitaw-crackdown-put-on-life-support-doctor|access-date=2021-02-10|website=Myanmar NOW|language=en}}</ref> Reports of injured protesters prompted the UN to issue a statement condemning the authority's violent [[use of force]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=2021-02-09|title=Nay Pyi Taw protesters shot, UN voices concern|url=https://www.mmtimes.com/news/nay-pyi-taw-protesters-shot-un-voices-concern.html|access-date=2021-02-09|website=The Myanmar Times}}</ref> In Yangon, soldiers were deployed to stand behind riot police.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Myanmar police fire rubber bullets as hundreds of thousands march|url=https://asia.nikkei.com/Spotlight/Myanmar-Coup/Myanmar-police-fire-rubber-bullets-as-hundreds-of-thousands-march|access-date=2021-02-09|website=Nikkei Asia|language=en-GB}}</ref>

